Q: Search x in rotated sorted array
Question Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/search-in-rotated-sorted-array/description/
Question Explanation:
Given an array which is rotated sorted(means is sorted and then rotated). And search the x.

Approach:
In a rotated sorted array, at least one side of mid is always sorted.
By identifying the sorted half and checking whether the target lies within its range,
we can discard the other half and continue binary search, achieving O(log n) time complexity.

T.C: O(logN), S.C: o(1)

Code:

class Solution {
    public int search(int[] arr, int x) {
        int n = arr.length;
        int low = 0;
        int high = n-1;
        int mid = low + (high-low)/2;
        while(high >= low){
            if(arr[mid] == x) return mid;
            // left part is sorted
            if(arr[mid] >= arr[low]){
                if(x >= arr[low] && x < arr[mid]) high = mid-1;
                else low = mid+1;
            }
            else {
                if(x > arr[mid] && x <= arr[high]) low = mid+1;
                else high = mid-1;
            }
            mid = low + (high-low)/2;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
